Description: [recto] Bruegel & Coecke.[Edouard] Michel, Bruegel, [Paris: Grès], 1931, citaat p. 39 N° 10; [verso][toegevoegde vermelding]: Michel assumes that Bruegel made 'une étude' 1550 or 1551, based on Coecke, and that this project served as prototype for Aertsen & Hemessen (!!?) F.G. The whole scheme with the composition rising to the right probably older (various artists, Brunswick Monogrammist, Bles?) and then B. may have used in addition Coecke and C. Bos.
